FBIS3-16581 "drsov053_f_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-053 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 National Affairs Fire Reported at Khmelnytskyy Nuclear Power Plant WS1703140394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1100 GMT 17 Mar 94 WS1703140394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] As the Ukrainian Interior Ministry General Fire Department has reported, on 16 March at 2045 [local time], a fire erupted in the engine room at the first power unit of the Khmelnytskyy nuclear power plant in a cable box housing power and control cables. The chiefs of the plant's fire department decided to deploy firefighters in the danger zone to extinguish the 6,000-volt cables. The firefighters wore special gear. In addition, to the firefighters' action, the plant personnel stopped the operation of the first power unit reactor. [passage indistinct] The fire was extinguished at 2110. The damages are currently being assessed. According to preliminary assessments, the fire was caused by a short circuit in the main power cable. The radiation level remains normal.
